Lekartów [lɛˈkartuf] (German: Mettich) is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Pietrowice Wielkie, within Racibórz County, Silesian Voivodeship, in southern Poland, close to the Czech border. It lies approximately 5 kilometres (3 mi) south-east of Pietrowice Wielkie, 8 km (5 mi) west of Racibórz, and 66 km (41 mi) west of the regional capital Katowice.
The village has a population of 280.